Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with 1/2 tsp @salt{1/2%tsp} for the macaroni. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3} (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{120%g}. Halve the @ciabatta{1}.

In a small #bowl{}, combine the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g}, half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and the @olive oil{2%tsp} for the crumb. Set the cheesy crumb aside.

Lay the ciabatta on a #baking tray{}, cut-side up. Spread over half the garlic and sprinkle over the remaining hard Italian cheese. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @macaroni{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the pan is hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the remaining garlic to the mushrooms and cook for ~{1%minute}, then lower the heat to medium.

Melt in the @butter{20%g}, then stir in the @plain flour{1.5%tbsp} and cook until it forms a paste, ~{1-2%minutes} - you've made a roux!

Stir in the @water{200%ml} a little at a time, followed by the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @vegetable stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer, stirring until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, preheat your #grill{} to high.

Once the sauce has thickened, remove from the heat and stir through the Cheddar and cooked macaroni.

Add a splash of water if it's a little thick. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Transfer the pasta to an #ovenproof dish{} and top with the cheesy crumb.

Place the mac and cheese on the baking tray with the garlic bread and grill until both are golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

When everything's ready, cut the garlic bread diagonally into triangles.

Share your ultimate mushroom mac and cheese between your #bowls{}, then sprinkle over the @truffle zest{1}.

Serve the cheesy garlic bread and @baby leaf mix{50%g} salad alongside. Drizzle the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} over the salad to finish.

> Enjoy the ultimate truffle mushroom mac and cheese experience with this extra special twist on a classic recipe!